unittitle_ssm: Anthony Mulvey-Reyes Collection of New York City LGBTQ+ Ephemera
abstract_ssm: The Anthony Mulvey-Reyes Collection of New York City LGBTQ+ Ephemera is a collection of approximately 111 pieces of ephemera from LGBTQ+ events and nightlife from 1991-1999 in New York City, especially Manhattan. Collected by Anthony Mulvey-Reyes, a gay Puerto Rican man, the bulk of the collection consists of invitations, ads, posters, and flyers for LGBTQ+ nightlife parties at institutions such as The Limelight, Sound Factory, and Tunnel.
